# Smart Proxy Enhancement Implementation Plan

> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.

**Goal:** Improve RTK's passthrough/proxy savings from ~40% to ~65% via smarter auto-filtering, add automatic output caching with diff for repeated commands, and add session repeat alerting.

**Architecture:** Three features building on existing infrastructure. (1) Enhance `auto_filter.rs` pipeline with build-output-aware noise stripping. (2) New `cache.rs` module using file-based storage with configurable TTL, wired into the proxy execution path. (3) Repeat detection using tracking DB timestamps, emitting stderr hints. Each feature is independent and can be tested in isolation.

**Tech Stack:** Rust, existing auto_filter/dedup/watch_cmd infrastructure, file-based cache, SQLite tracking DB.

