### Task 2: Enhance Auto-Filter вЂ” Strip Blank Lines, Decorative Separators, CR Lines

**Files:**
- Modify: `src/auto_filter.rs` (add pipeline stages before dedup)

**What to change in `filter_with_status()`:**

After ANSI strip (step 1), before noise dedup (step 2), add:

```rust
// 1.5. Strip carriage-return overwritten lines (keep last version only)
let clean = strip_cr_overwrites(&clean);

// 1.6. Strip decorative separators and excessive blank lines
let clean = strip_decorative(&clean);
```

**Add helper functions** in `auto_filter.rs`:

```rust
/// Strip lines overwritten by carriage return (progress bars, spinners).
/// Only keeps the final version of each line group.
fn strip_cr_overwrites(output: &str) -> String {
    output
        .lines()
        .map(|line| {
            // If line contains \r, only keep content after last \r
            if let Some(pos) = line.rfind('\r') {
                &line[pos + 1..]
            } else {
                line
            }
        })
        .collect::<Vec<_>>()
        .join("\n")
}

/// Strip decorative separators (в•ђв•ђв•ђ, в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ, ***, etc.) and collapse
/// runs of 3+ blank lines into a single blank line.
fn strip_decorative(output: &str) -> String {
    lazy_static::lazy_static! {
        static ref DECORATOR: regex::Regex =
            regex::Regex::new(r"^[\s=в”Ђв”Ѓ\-\*~_в•Њв•Ќв”„в”…в”€в”‰]{4,}\s*$").unwrap();
    }
    let mut result = Vec::new();
    let mut blank_count = 0u32;

    for line in output.lines() {
        if line.trim().is_empty() {
            blank_count += 1;
            if blank_count <= 2 {
                result.push(line);
            }
        } else if DECORATOR.is_match(line) {
            // Skip decorative lines entirely
        } else {
            blank_count = 0;
            result.push(line);
        }
    }

    result.join("\n")
}
```

**Steps:**
1. Read `src/auto_filter.rs`
